        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-23 14:53:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI need to see proposed examples of the new util code usage in the reference dataform, otherwise can not estimate it's usefullness",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "2e12bd9980c4100f58185c5108a1b40ed8fcbf2c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1089,
          "name": "Sandeep Jha",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "sandeejh@in.ibm.com",
          "username": "Sandeep4029"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-23 17:26:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nOleg, it will be difficult to explain you the plan for all the functions in the util file. I will give an example for one of the functions for now, so that you have a basic idea about what plan i have. \n\nThe function decideExtension is there currently in reference-dataform.component.ts, I want to move that function to this util ts file to remove redundancy in the code also improve the code reusablilty. \nSimilarly, currently in reference-dataform.component.ts, we have a function called \"prepareArtifactList\". Inside this method, at a lot of places, there is redundant code for forming artifact names for param/template/PD. We can have that code in the util class and use it there using the \"createArtifactName\" method in util class. \nFor eg, \nlet config_template_fileName = this.referenceDataObject.action + '_' + scopeName + '_' + '0.0.1V.' + extension;\nThe above line in reference-dataform.util.ts will be changed to the following using \"createArtifactName\" method in util class.\nlet config_template_fileName = this.referenceDataFormUtil.createArtifactName(this.referenceDataObject.action, vnf, type, extension);\n\nSo, I hope I am clear with my point. I am basically trying to centralize the redundant piece of code from reference-dataform.component.ts to a common util file for reference data module called reference-dataform.util.ts .",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
